{
  "doc_id": "14971",
  "text": "The IR has been reported to be independently lost at least five times among seed plants, two of which are within rosids [CITATION_1] . In addition to the inverted repeat lacking clade (IRLC) of papilionoid Fabaceae [CITATION_2] and Erodium of Gerantiaceae [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , the IR was found to be lost in two lineages of Fragaria (Rosaceae), which are F. vesca ssp. bracteatea and F. mandschurica (accession: NC_018767, not shown in Figure 2 ). Based on the Fragaria phylogeny shown in a previous study [CITATION_5] , it seems that IR loss was not a single event in Fragaria.",
